detailed_profile.about: With over 20 years of experience in office administration and professional organizing, I am passionate about creating efficient and productive work environments that support the goals and vision of the organization. As the Office Manager at Capital First Trust, a leading provider of trust and custodial services, I manage the daily operations of the office, oversee the IT department, manage Accounts Payable and coordinate with various departments and external partners. I worked as in-house Project Manager for the build out and move to our new location. In addition to my current role, I am also the owner-operator of Help Me Rhonda Unlimited, LLC, a professional organizing and contract assistant service that offers customized solutions for home and office organization, event planning, paper and file management, moving help, and charity donation drop off. I also have a military background, as I served as a Flight Operations Resource Management Air Reserve Technician and Reservist at the United States Air Force for nine years, where I was responsible for training and monitoring reservists, as well as performing various tasks related to flight operations and resource management. Through these diverse experiences, I have developed and honed skills such as communication, teamwork, leadership, problem-solving, and adaptability.

In 2013, First Capital significantly expanded its services to include serving as fiduciary for "Advisor Directed Trusts" including and especially South Dakota situs trusts.

In my role as Trust Case Manager, I work diligently to assist in business development and new account on boarding. I specialize in Advisor Directed Trust account set up ("Wealth Management"), especially existing trust transfers. I work to establish, maintain and grow relationships with trust partners including advisor firms, RIAs, broker dealers, custodial firms, etc. I also specialize in large volume management and organization, simultaneously juggling over 120 new incoming accounts totaling more than $77 million in assets each individually on-boarded over a period of 16 months. It was during that time I also worked to develop various new installation processes specific to advisor directed trusts and transferring trust accounts including specific processes for individual broker dealers and custodians.

As part of the marketing and business development department, I take part in preparing marketing materials including brochures, newsletters, PowerPoint presentations, and informational packets for distribution. In addition, I have also been involved with special projects around the office including overseeing a large, long-term data collection project. I also work within the First Capital team to develop in-house training programs and best practices while training and cross training colleagues across a variety of departments/responsibilities.

detailed_profile.name: Eduardo Saverin
detailed_profile.position: Co-Founder, Facebook Inc.
detailed_profile.about: I am a co-founder and the first investor of Facebook Inc., a company which from its humble beginnings in early 2004 as a Harvard-only student social network has emerged today as a business and cultural touchstone. As a 21-year old college student, I made the first seed investment into Facebook with the majority of my life savings. I am thankful and humbled to have played a part in Facebook’s remarkable transition from a then one-college specific social network to the most ubiquitous social utility in the world today, empowering more than 1 billion people of all age groups, geographies, languages and cultural affinities to share and make the world a more open and connected place. Today, through my venture capital firm, B Capital Group, I have the pleasure of working with and investing in entrepreneurs who are looking to change the world. As an investor and mentor, I work closely with an array of companies of all sizes and stages, from all parts of the world, that share one common thread: passion for cross-platform people-centric innovation with pan-global ambitions. On my spare time, I cannot get myself to stop playing chess and reading up on meteorology, amongst other things. I was born in Sao Paulo, Brazil and graduated with a degree Economics with honors from Harvard University in 2006. I currently reside in Singapore.
